[4] Michigan update
Date: Wed 17 Apr 2019
Source: mLive [abridged, edited]
https://www.mlive.com/news/2019/04/michigans-measles-outbreak-continues-to-grow-with-42-cases-now-reported.html


The state health department added another reported case in Oakland County to the list Wednesday afternoon [17 Apr 2019]. While there is an additional measles case to report, there are not any new exposure spots, as of now.

Michigan's current measles outbreak continues to trend in the wrong direction, with the state health department reporting 42 cases as of Wednesday morning, [17 Apr 2019].

While the 2 new cases added to the list come in previously affected Wayne and Oakland counties, one of the cases is linked to exposure spots in Kent and Ingham counties.

The Department of Health and Human Services reports in a news release that the outbreak has caused 39 cases in Oakland County, 2 in Wayne County, including one in Detroit, and one in Washtenaw County.

[Byline: Benjamin Raven]

